{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} [[File:Wodan Heilt Balders Pferd by Emil Doepler.jpg|thumb|A scene from one of the [[Merseburg Incantations]]: gods [[Wōden|Wodan]] and [[Balder]] stand before the goddesses [[Sól (sun)|Sunna]], [[Sinthgunt]], [[Fulla|Volla]], and [[Frigg|Friia]] ([[Emil Doepler]], 1905)]] In [[Germanic paganism]], the indigenous religion of the ancient [[Germanic peoples]] who inhabited [[Germanic peoples|Germanic Europe]], there were [[polytheism|a number of different gods and goddesses]]. Germanic deities are attested from numerous sources, including works of literature, various chronicles, [[Runic alphabet|runic inscriptions]], personal names, place names, and other sources. This article contains a comprehensive '''list of Germanic deities''' outside the numerous Germanic [[Matres and Matronae]] inscriptions from the 1st to 5th century CE.
