'''Marcelline Pauper''' (born 1663) was one of the [[Sisters of Charity of Nevers]]. She asked to receive the [[stigmata]] as repayment for a [[sacrilege]] committed at the Sister's chapel, and received them on 26 April 1702.<ref name="imbert">{{cite book|last=Imbert-Gourbeyre|first=Antoine|title=La stigmatisation: 1894|year=1996|publisher=Editions Jérôme Millon|isbn=978-2-84137-035-1|pages=365–67|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y_qYn6uax7AC&pg=PA367|author2=Joachim Bouflet|accessdate=29 December 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Summers|first=Montague|title=History of Witchcraft and Demonology|year=1926|pages=145–46|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_95KgSNPkXYC&pg=PA145|authorlink=Montague Summers|accessdate=29 December 2010}}</ref> 

Pauper's autobiography was not published until 1871.<ref>{{cite book|last=DeJean|first=Joan|title=Tender geographies: women and the origins of the novel in France|year=1991|publisher=Columbia UP|isbn=978-0-231-06230-5|pages=215|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hC3dbiVHD3sC&pg=PA215}}</ref>

