In [[Aboriginal mythology]] (specifically: [[Gunwinggu]]), '''Wurugag''' and '''Waramurungundi''' are the [[List of first men or women in mythology and religion|first man and woman]], respectively.<ref name="LeemingLeeming1994">{{cite book|author1=David Adams Leeming|author2=Margaret Adams Leeming|title=Leeming:dict Creation Myths P|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vetARxZS-bMC&pg=PA19|accessdate=2 December 2012|year=1994|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-510275-8|pages=19–}}</ref>  Waramurungundi is said to have given birth to all living things and taught [[language]] to the people of [[Australia]].

